prompt:
Your task is to answer the user's question using available tools. 
You have access to the following tools:
Name: Apache Superset
Description: API to manage your BI dashboards and data sources on Superset
Documentation:
createDashboard: Create a new dashboard
Parameters: {"dashboardName": "string. The name of the new dashboard.", "description": "string. A brief description of the dashboard.", "charts": "Array[string]. A list of charts to be included in the dashboard initially."}
Output: Successful creation of the dashboard.
 - Format: application/json
 - Structure: #CreateDashboardResponse
updateDashboard: Modify an existing dashboard
Parameters: {"dashboardId": "integer. The unique ID of the dashboard to be modified.", "dashboardName": "string. The new name of the dashboard.", "description": "string. A new description for the dashboard.", "charts": "Array[string]. A list of charts to be added or removed from the dashboard."}
Output: Successful update of the dashboard.
 - Format: application/json
 - Structure: #UpdateDashboardResponse
deleteDashboard: Delete an existing dashboard
Parameters: {"dashboardId": "Required. integer. The unique ID of the dashboard to be deleted."}
Output: Successful deletion of the dashboard.
 - Format: application/json
 - Structure: #DeleteDashboardResponse
createDataSource: Create a new data source
Parameters: {"sourceName": "string. The name of the new data source.", "connectionString": "string. The connection string to connect to the data source.", "type": "string. The type of the data source (e.g., 'mysql', 'postgresql', etc.)."}
Output: Successful creation of the data source.
 - Format: application/json
 - Structure: #CreateDataSourceResponse
updateDataSource: Modify an existing data source
Parameters: {"sourceId": "integer. The unique ID of the data source to be modified.", "sourceName": "string. The new name of the data source.", "connectionString": "string. The new connection string to connect to the data source.", "type": "string. The new type of the data source."}
Output: Successful update of the data source.
 - Format: application/json
 - Structure: #UpdateDataSourceResponse
deleteDataSource: Delete an existing data source
Parameters: {"sourceId": "Required. integer. The unique ID of the data source to be deleted."}
Output: Successful deletion of the data source.
 - Format: application/json
 - Structure: #DeleteDataSourceResponse
managePermissions: Manage permissions for dashboards and data sources
Parameters: {"targetId": "integer. The unique ID of the dashboard or data source for which permissions are to be managed.", "targetType": "string. The type of the target ('dashboard' or 'data source').", "permissions": "Array[string]. A list of permissions to be granted or revoked.", "users": "Array[string]. A list of users for which the permissions are to be managed."}
Output: Successful management of permissions.
 - Format: application/json
 - Structure: #ManagePermissionsResponse
configureAlerts: Configure email notifications for data alerts and updates
Parameters: {"email": "string. The email address to which notifications are to be sent.", "frequency": "string. The frequency at which notifications are to be sent ('daily', 'weekly', 'monthly', etc.)."}
Output: Successful configuration of alerts.
 - Format: application/json
 - Structure: #ConfigureAlertsResponse
embedDashboard: Embed a dashboard into another application
Parameters: {"dashboardId": "integer. The unique ID of the dashboard to be embedded.", "targetApp": "string. The name of the application into which the dashboard is to be embedded."}
Output: Successful embedding of the dashboard.
 - Format: application/json
 - Structure: #EmbedDashboardResponse

The detailed output format for the tools is outlined below:
#CreateDashboardRequest: Object{dashboardName, description, charts: Array[string]}
#CreateDashboardResponse: Object{dashboardId, dashboardURL}
#UpdateDashboardRequest: Object{dashboardId, dashboardName, description, charts: Array[string]}
#UpdateDashboardResponse: Object{dashboardId, dashboardName, description, charts: Array[string]}
#DeleteDashboardResponse: Object{message}
#CreateDataSourceRequest: Object{sourceName, connectionString, type}
#CreateDataSourceResponse: Object{sourceId}
#UpdateDataSourceRequest: Object{sourceId, sourceName, connectionString, type}
#UpdateDataSourceResponse: Object{sourceId, sourceName, connectionString, type}
#DeleteDataSourceResponse: Object{message}
#ManagePermissionsRequest: Object{targetId, targetType, permissions: Array[string], users: Array[string]}
#ManagePermissionsResponse: Object{message}
#ConfigureAlertsRequest: Object{email, frequency}
#ConfigureAlertsResponse: Object{message}
#EmbedDashboardRequest: Object{dashboardId, targetApp}
#EmbedDashboardResponse: Object{embedCode}

Use the following format:
Thought: you should always think about what to do
Action: the action to take, should be one of the tool names.
Action Input: the input to the action, must be in JSON format. All of the action input must be realistic and from the user.

Begin! Question: It seems like the connection string for data source ID 85 has changed. Can you update it with the new string "postgres://user:password@newhost/dbname"? Also, change its name to "Updated Sales Data".

